      • make

        public static <A extends KeyableBean,B extends java.lang.Comparable<? super B>> SetRestriction<A,B> make(@Nonnull
                                                                                         java.lang.Class<A> type,
                                                                                         @Nonnull
                                                                                         PersistentPath<A,B> path,
                                                                                         @Nonnull
                                                                                         InOperation inOp,
                                                                                         @Nonnull
                                                                                         java.lang.Iterable<B> set)
                                                                                            throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                                                                                                   java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Creates and returns a new restriction with the specified parameters. The iterable will be reduced to a set internally, thus it is unnecessary to filter duplicates before calling this method.

        For CompareNotIn, this method will return entities with null leaf values, if null is not contained in the set. Additionally, when filtering MonetaryAmounts, this will exclude values with different currencies from those in set.

        Type Parameters:
        A - Root type of the path. Must be an entity type.
        B - Leaf type of the path. Must be a comparable type.
        Parameters:
        type - type of restriction to create.
        path - value for Path.
        inOp - type of comparison (CompareIn or CompareNotIn).
        set - value for Set.
        Returns:
        a set comparison restriction.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if type, path, inOp, or set is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if set contains MonetaryAmounts with mismatched currencies.
